d enhanced audio and picture quality Unlike the original releases, these sets include three to four 22-minute episodes, instead of two. They also feature new cover art, as opposed to previous releases which used the cover art for the corresponding series book. Many of the previously released titles have been re-released as well, but only new releases are included in this list. Out of all of these dvd releases, 69 out of the 74 episodes episodes have been released on dvd in the united states, exluding the Haunted Mask parts 1 and 2 werewolf skin parts 1 and 2 and the Cuckoo clock of doom. the haunted mask and werewolf skin however were previously released on vhs. \n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Release name\n! UK release date<br />(region 2)\n! Australian release date<br />(region 4)\n! North American release date<br />(region 1)\n! Notes\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|| ''[[A Night in Terror Tower]]''\n|| \u2013\n|| \u2013\n|| 16 September 2008<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B001B1UO80/ |title=Goosebumps: A Night in Terror Tower: Artist Not Provided: Movies & TV |publisher=Amazon.com |date= |accessdate=7 December 2009}}</ref>\n|| Also contains ''[[Stay Out of the Basement]]''\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|| ''[[Monster Blood]]''\n|| \u2013\n|| \u2013\n|| 16 September 2008<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B001B1UO8K/ |title=Goosebumps: Monster Blood: Artist Not Provided: Movies & TV |publisher=Amazon.com |date= |accessdate=7 December 2009}}</ref>\n|| Also contains ''More Monster Blood'', ''[[How to Kill a Monster]]'', and ''[[The Girl Who Cried Monster]]''\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|| ''[[One Day at HorrorLand]]''\n|| \u2013\n|| \u2013\n|| 16 September 2008<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B001B1UO8A/ |title=Goosebumps: One Day at Horrorland: Artist Not Provided: Movies & TV |publisher=Amazon.com |date= |accessdate=7 December 2009}}</ref>\n|| Also contains ''[[Welcome To Camp Nightmare]]''\n|- style=\"text-align:cent