''\n|| 26 November 2012<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/Goosebumps-Season-One-DVD-Stine/dp/B0095WN8D0/ |title=Goosebumps: Season One |publisher=Amazon.co.uk |date= |accessdate=7 December 2012}}</ref>\n||\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|| ''Season Two''\n|| 25 March 2013<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/Goosebumps-Season-2-DVD/dp/B00A7SFWHG |title=Goosebumps: Season Two |publisher=Amazon.co.uk |date= |accessdate=7 December 2012}}</ref>\n||\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|| ''Seasons Three and Four''\n|| 19 August 2013<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/Goosebumps-Season-3-4-DVD/dp/B00A7SFVYU/ |title=Goosebumps: Seasons Three & Four |publisher=Amazon.co.uk |date= |accessdate=7 December 2012}}</ref>\n||\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|| ''The Complete Collection''\n|| 28 October 2013<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/Goosebumps-The-Complete-Collection-DVD/dp/B00E2037DG/ref=sr_1_1?s=dvd&ie=UTF8&qid=1374788162&sr=1-1&keywords=goosebumps|title=Goosebumps: The Complete Collection [DVD]|work=Amazon.co.uk|accessdate=25 July 2013}}</ref>\n||\n|}\n\nOn 2 April 2014, [[Madman Entertainment]] released the entire series in four DVD sets as well as a \"Most Wanted Collection\" in Australia and New Zealand (DVD region 4).\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Release name\n! Release date\n! Notes\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|| ''Season One''\n|| 4 February 2014<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.madman.com.au/catalogue/view/22460/goosebumps-season-1|title=Goosebumps: Season One |publisher=madman.com.au|date= |accessdate=4 February 2014}}</ref>\n||\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|| ''Season Two''\n|| 7 May 2014<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.madman.com.au/catalogue/view/22718/goosebumps-season-2 |title=Goosebumps: Season Two |publisher=madman.com.au|date= |accessdate=7 May 2014}}</ref>\n||\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|| ''Season Three''\n|| 4 June 2014<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.madman.com.au/catalogue/view/23113/goosebumps-season-3 |title=Goosebumps: Season Three |publisher=madman.com.au|date= |accessdate=4 June 2014}}</ref>\n||\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|| ''Season Four''\n|| 9 July 2014<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.madman.com.au/catalogue/view/23448/goosebumps-season-4-final-season/ref=sr_1_1?s=dvd&ie=UTF8&qid=1374788162&sr=1-1&keywords=goosebumps|title=Goosebumps: Season Four [DVD]|work=madman.com.au|accessdate=9 July 2014}}</ref>\n||\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|| ''Goosebumps - Most Wanted''\n|| 9 July 2014<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.madman.com.au/catalogue/view/23449/goosebumps-most-wanted/ref=sr_1_1?s=dvd&ie=UTF8&qid=1374788162&sr=1-1&keywords=goosebumps|title=Goosebumps - Most Wanted [DVD]|work=madman.com.au|accessdate=9 July 2014}}</ref>\n||\n|}\n\n===Online===\n* The complete series is now on iTunes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/tv-season/goosebumps-season-1/id331946069 |title=Goosebumps, Season 1 |publisher=itunes.apple.com |accessdate=1 October 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110519181814/http://itunes.apple.com/us/tv-season/goosebumps-season-1/id331946069 |archivedate=19 May 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/tv-season/goosebumps-season-2/id332081966 |title=Goosebumps, Season 2 |publisher=itunes.apple.com |accessdate=1 October 2011 }}{{dead link|date=March 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/tv-season/goosebumps-season-3/id382070658 |title=Goosebumps, Season 3 |publisher=itunes.apple.com |accessdate=1 October 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110519155440/http://itunes.apple.com/us/tv-season/goosebumps-season-3/id382070658 |archivedate=19 May 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/tv-season/goosebumps-season-4/id382072967 |title=Goosebumps, Season 4 |publisher=itunes.apple.com |accessdate=1 October 2011 }}{{dead link|date=March 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n* The series is available for streaming on [[Netflix]] (United States, United Kingdom, and Canada).<ref>{{cite web|title=Every Goosebumps episode ever is now streaming on Netflix |url=https://www.engadget.com/2013/08/15/goosebumps-now-streaming-netflix-omg-dudes/|publisher=Engadget|accessdate=15 August 2013}}</ref>\n\n==''Goosebumps Presents''==\nThe books in the [[Goosebumps (original series)|original ''Goosebumps'' series]]  that were made into episodes of the ''Goosebumps'' television series were subsequently re-released in a series called ''Goosebumps Presents''. The main difference between the books in this series and their original publications is that the ''Goosebumps Presents'' editions contained photos from the corresponding episodes. Eighteen books were released from 1996 to 1998.\n\n<onlyinclude>{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! width=\"30\" style=\"background:#58c035;color:#fff;\"|# !!  style=\"background:#58c035;color:#fff;\"|Title !! width=\"150\" style=\"background:#58c035;color:#fff;\"|Original published date !! style=\"background:#58c035;color:#fff;\"|Pages !! width=\"130\" style=\"background:#58c035;color:#fff;\"|ISBN\n{{Book list/sublist\n |main_list = List of Goosebumps books\n |book_number = 01\n |title = ''The Girl Who Cried Monster''\n |title_align = left\n |publish_date = 5 February 1996\n |short_summary = Telling so many tall-tale [[monster]] stories that she is disgusting her friends and family, Lucy Dark does not know what to do when she discovers a \"real\" monster in the summer reading program [[librarian]].\n |isbn = 0-590-74586-7\n |aux1 = 57\n |line_color = #58c035\n}}\n{{Book list/sublist\n |main_list = List of Goosebumps books\n |book_number = 02\n |title = ''The Cuckoo Clock of Doom''\n |title_align = left\n |publish_date = 20 May 1996\n |short_summary = Deciding to get even with his bratty little [[sister]], who always gets him in trouble, Michael Webster fiddles wit